author: COMSOL
description: This example simulates the flow of a suspension placed between two concentric cylinders. The inner cylinder rotates while the outer is fixed. The suspension is dense, that is, the volume fraction of solid particles is high. The model accounts for buoyancy effects and shear-induced migration.
